05/03/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The army is expected to end compulsory service by September and align its recruitment processes with NATO standards, according to media reports Thursday (March 5th).
Currently, all Albanian men between the ages of 18 and 26 must complete 18 months of compulsory service or pay a fine.
In other news, the French senate ratified the protocol for Albania's NATO membership on Wednesday.
The Albanian Foreign Ministry said it expects the same move from Luxembourg and the Netherlands.
(Shekulli, Koha Jone, Balkan Web, Top News - 05/03/09)
